headline: Wheels Up to Present at Barclays Industrial Select Conference
summary: Wheels Up Experience Inc. (NYSE: UP), one of the world's leading providers of on-demand private aviation, today announced that the company's Chief Executive Officer, George Mattson, will present in person at the Barclays Industrial Select Conference in Miami, FL on Thursday, February 19, 2026 at 10:25am ET.

headline: Can American Airlines turn itself around?
summary: American Airlines has promised Wall Street and travelers that 2026 will be a turnaround year. It’s been trailing its U.S. competitors Delta Air Lines and United Airlines in profits and reliability by a wide margin and has fallen behind in the race for premium air travel. So the pressure is on for CEO Robert Isom.

headline: Boeing Orders And Defense Wins Test Valuation Gap And Labor Risks
summary: In January, Boeing reported one of its strongest recent months for aircraft orders and deliveries, including a substantial widebody order from Delta Air Lines. The company secured significant long term U.S. Air Force contracts tied to C-17A fleet upgrades. Boeing announced plans for a new 737 Max assembly line while unions raised concerns about potential job relocations to South Carolina.
